  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Project requirements (PR-HEM-001 through PR-HEM-007) are referenced throughout this narrative to establish traceability; the model has been evaluated against those requirements in the supporting technical report.",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cou1-hemolysis-worst-case",
